title.rendered: Pretoria vs Durban, South Africa T20 League, 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Pretoria: Philip Salt (wk), Kusal Mendis, Theunis de Bruyn, Rilee Rossouw, Shane Dadswell, James Neesham, Wayne Parnell (c), Senuran Muthusamy, Eathan Bosch, Anrich Nortje, Joshua Little

Durban: Ben McDermott, Quinton de Kock (c), Matthew Breetzke, Wiaan Mulder, Heinrich Klaasen (wk), Dwaine Pretorius, David Willey, Keemo Paul, Simon Harmer, Keshav Maharaj, Reece Topley

Venue: SuperSport Park, Centurion

Pitch Report

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score: 166

2nd innings average score: 176

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

In Centurion, Quinton de Kock has collected 525 runs at 44 including the highest score of 108. In addition, he has inflicted 9 dismissals with the gloves.

Heinrich Klaasen has decent numbers at SuperSport Park. He has added 443 runs at 32 including the highest score of 69.

Anrich Nortje has gone wicketless only once in this league. Overall, he has taken 15 wickets, including the best figures of 3 for 13, which came in Centurion.

When these teams met earlier, Will Jacks (56 off 25) and Senuran Muthusamy (3 for 12) were the captain and vice-captain of the Ultimate Team respectively.

Dwaine Pretorius is yet to go wicketless in this competition, owing to which he has been a part of the Ultimate Team on 4 of 5 occasions.

Rilee Rossouw has managed only 86 runs in 8 games this season.

All 3 three-wicket hauls at Centurion in the last 3 games have been bagged by the seamers.

In the same period, an average of 8 sixes per innings have been launched at the venue.
